functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: When were each of the New Seven Wonders of the World constructed?
When were each of the New Seven Wonders of the World constructed?

The New Seven Wonders of the World were constructed at different times, spanning several centuries. Here's the list:

1. Great Wall of China: The construction of the Great Wall began around the 5th century BCE and continued for over 2 millennia, with most of the current wall being built during the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644 CE).

2. Petra, Jordan: The ancient city of Petra was established around 300 BCE as the capital of the Nabataean Kingdom. Its construction continued until around 100 CE.

3. Christ the Redeemer, Brazil: This Art Deco-style statue was designed by Heitor da Silva Costa and sculpted by Paul Landowski. It was constructed between 1922 and 1931.

4. Machu Picchu, Peru: Built in the 15th century, around 1450 CE, Machu Picchu is believed to have been constructed as an estate for the Inca emperor Pachacuti.

5. Chichén Itzá, Mexico: The construction of this Mayan city started around the 5th century CE, with most of the significant structures being built between the 9th and 13th centuries CE.

6. Colosseum, Italy: Also known as the Flavian Amphitheatre, the Colosseum was constructed between 70 and 80 CE under the Flavian emperors.

7. Taj Mahal, India: Commissioned by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan, the Taj Mahal was built between 1632 and 1653 as a mausoleum for his wife, Mumtaz Mahal.

These construction dates provide a glimpse into the rich historical and cultural heritage associated with each of these iconic wonders.
